Taiwan Stocks: AU Optronics, Chimei Innolux. Vanguard, Wistron

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-03-09T02:30:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/au-optronics-largan-nanya-technology-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Stocks of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:41 a.m. local time, unless
stated otherwise.  The Taiex Index rose 53.96, or 0.6 percent, to 8,801.71.  Flat panel companies:  Chimei Innolux Corp. (3481)  (3481 TT) gained
1.2 percent to NT$34.10.  AU Optronics Corp. (2409)  (2409 TT) advanced
1.9 percent to NT$27.55.  Taiwan will allow Chimei and other domestic flat-panel
makers to acquire stakes in Chinese peers or merge with them,
Hwang Jung-chiou, a deputy minister at the Ministry of Economic
Affairs, said in Taipei yesterday. The panel makers will also be
permitted to start factories on the mainland based on the same
generation of technology used in plants in Taiwan, he said.    Vanguard International Semiconductor Corp. (5347)  (5347 TT): The
chipmaker cut its first-quarter guidance because of higher-than-
expected inventory from its clients, the Hsinchu, Taiwan-based
company said in an exchange statement yesterday. The stock sank
6.1 percent to NT$15.4.    Wistron Corp. (3231)  (3231 TT) retreated 1.3 percent to NT$55.50.
The laptop maker was lowered to “neutral” from “overweight”
at JPMorgan Chase & Co. by Alvin Kwock, an analyst at the
brokerage. The 12-month share-price estimate is NT$60.  To contact the reporter on this story:
